14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-101.6b, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 6-101.6b. A. For purposes of this section, "teacher":
20 1. "Teacher" means the term as defined in paragraph 1 of
21 Section 1-116 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title; and
22 2. "Support employee" means the term as defined in paragraph 9
23 of Section 1-116 of this title.
24
HB1483 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 B. No school district shall prohibit or take disciplinary
2 action against teachers or support employees for:
3 1. Disclosing public information to correct what the teacher or
4 support employee reasonably believes evidences a violation of the
5 Oklahoma Constitution or law or a rule promulgated pursuant to law;
6 2. Reporting a violation of the Oklahoma Constitution or state
7 or federal law; or
8 3. Taking any of the above actions without giving prior notice
9 to the teacher's or support employee's supervisor or anyone else in
10 the teacher's relevant chain of command.
11 C. For the purposes of this section, "reporting" means
12 providing a spoken or written account to a supervising teacher,
13 administrator, school board member, representative from the State
14 Department of Education, law enforcement official, district
15 attorney, and/or parent or legal guardian of a student directly
16 impacted by the actions.
17 D. Each school district shall prominently post or publish a
18 copy of this section of law in locations where it can reasonably be
19 expected to come to the attention of all teachers and support
20 employees.
21 E. Nothing in this section shall be construed to allow a
22 teacher or support employee to violate students' or parents' rights
23 to confidentiality and protection under the Family Educational
24 Rights and Privacy Act of 1974 (FERPA).
HB1483 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
2 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
3 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
4 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
5 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
6
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION OVERSIGHT, dated
03/05/2025 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
